{Vegetation}
There is an unusual copse North of Two Bridges called Wistman's Wood. There are records of this existing as long ago as the seventeenth century.
Ecologists think that Wistman's Wood is part of an old forest that covered most of the area. It is made up of gnarled, stunted Oak trees amidst a granite clitter covered in Lichen, Moss and Ferns.
{Wildlife}
Kestrels, Buzzards and Crows are often seen in the vicinity of the wood. Larks are often heard but seldom seen. Sheep, cattle and ponies graze out on the open moor.
